        <h1 align="center">COC IEP 200 Lesson Plan for Tue 5 Mar 2013</h1>
        <p class="tagline"> 2012/13 Winter Trimester Block 3 Lesson #9</p>

<h2>NEWS & CURRENT EVENTS</h2>

<p>09:30 to 10:15 (45 minutes) | Learning Objective (1): Reading & Vocabulary - Read independently and recognize the main idea and most details of a passage. | Learning Objective (2): Listening & Speaking – Comprehend spoken, informal questions at a moderate level.
</p>
<ul>
<li>Students discuss their summaries of the “Vatican Must Choose New Pope to Lead Catholic Church" News for You article with partners 
</li>
<li>Students complete the teacher's guide comprehension with their partners
</li>
<li>Read and discuss the article as a class
</li>
</ul>

<h2>CHECK-IN</h2>

<p>10:20 to 10:45 (25)
</p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in Student's Homework
</li>
<li>Ask students “Do you have any questions for me?”
</li>
<li>Review Quiz 2
</li>
<li>Look over Quiz 3 Study Guide (Download PDF at http://www.danoff.org/leftinfront/wp-content/plugins/download-monitor/download.php?id=60 or http://is.gd/HoM0QT)
</li>
<li>Discuss last night's video assignment
</li>
</ul>

<h2>GRAMMAR IN CONTEXT</h2>

<p>10:45 to 11:15 (30)
</p>
<ul>
<li>Read and review pages 67 to 70
</li>
</ul>

<h2>CHICAGO CULTURAL RESEARCH POSTER PROJECT</h2>
<p>11:15 to 11:45 (30)</p>
  		<ul>
			<li>Essay - Review results pargraph; introduce discussion and conclusion paragraphs</li>
			<li>Poster - Introduce poster</li>
			</ul>

<h2>Comic Book</h2>
<p>11:45 to 12:15 (30)</p>
<ul>
		<li>Continue Fantom of the Fair story</li>
</ul>

<h2>Short Story</h2>
<p>13:00 to 14:15 (65)</p>
<ul>
		<li>Start the "Frozen Pizza" story</li>
</ul>

<h2>Student Learning Logs</h2>
<ul>
		<li>Before students leave they have to write an entry in their learning logs</li>
</ul>

              <h2>Homework</h2>
              <dl>
                <dt>To Read</dt>
                <dd>
                  <ol>
                    <li>Review Frozen Pizza and other slices of life: pages 39 to 41</li>
                    <li>News Hour: "Names from the Past Lead to Battles in South" <a href="#nfy">News for You</a> article</li>
                  </ol>
                </dd>
                <dt>To Watch</dt>
                <dd>
                  <ol>
                    <li>"ESL Verb English Grammar Vocabulary Rap Song EL-T-Funk Present Tense with Fluency MC!" YouTube video (Short URL is <a href="http://is.gd/cociep200video2">http://is.gd/cociep200video2</a>. Long URL is <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Xfyur6CB7M">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Xfyur6CB7M</a>.</li>
